===Adjective===
{{en-adj|er}}

# [[cheerful|Cheerful]] and [[happy]]; [[smiling]].

===Noun===
[[Image:Smiley_head_happy.png|80px|thumb|A '''smiley'''.]]
{{en-noun|s|smilies}}

# {{context|rare|lang=en}} A simplified representation of a smiling face.
# {{context|Internet|lang=en}} A sequence of keyboard characters used to represent a person's mood or emotion, especially <tt>[[Unsupported titles/Colon right paren|:)]]</tt> or <tt>[[Unsupported titles/Colon hyphen right paren|:-)]]</tt> or other smiling depiction.
# {{context|slang|lang=en}} Having one's throat slit from side to side.
# {{context|rare|lang=en}} An improvised street weapon consisting of a length of chain with padlocks and other heavy objects affixed to one end.
# {{cx|South Africa|lang=en}} A [[roast]]ed [[sheep]]'s [[head]].

'''Note:''' The variant spelling "[[smilie]]" is rare, but the plural form "[[smilies]]" (which is properly the plural of "smilie" or "smily", not "smiley") is common.

